      "properties": {
        "Node name for S&R": "Note"
      },
      "widgets_values": [
        "WAN 2.2 → HDR — recommended path (v3.1.2+)\n\n• HDR conversion runs on the MATH path: for multi-frame video the\n  SDR→HDR Universal node intentionally skips RUDRA learned\n  reconstruction (WAN's video VAE compresses 81→21 frames, and the\n  current wan/ltx/hunyuan RUDRA checkpoints were trained on T=1\n  stills). Leave the node's optional 'vae' input DISCONNECTED for\n  video — connecting it just logs a skip notice.\n• adaptive knee 0.75 + temporal_smoothing 0.85 = flicker-free\n  highlight expansion; raise shoulder_gamma toward 2.0 if only\n  speculars should expand.\n• Linear output → EXR (16-bit half) is the grading master;\n  the PQ branch is a delivery/QC check (preview looks dim — that's\n  PQ, view on an HDR monitor or via the Radiance HDR Monitor node).\n• For stills: single-frame input + connected VAE + a trained RUDRA\n  checkpoint enables learned highlight reconstruction."
      ],
      "title": "READ ME — WAN 2.2 HDR"
    }
